# Workspace Hygiene

Use this when a project creates large generated output, worktrees, caches, or
temporary artifacts.

Workspace rule source:

- `..\..\System\docs\workspace-hygiene.md`
- `..\..\System\scripts\workspace-hygiene-check.ps1`

## Local Contract

- Keep source, durable reports, user state, and expensive generated outputs.
- Treat caches, build output, extracted duplicates, and abandoned worktrees as
  cleanup candidates only after classification.
- Take a rescue snapshot before cleaning uncommitted or user-visible work.
- Do not delete H/W/I project folders outside the active scope.

Run from the Tools root:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\System\scripts\workspace-hygiene-check.ps1 -Json
```
